# Copy to .env and fill in from Supabase → Project Settings → API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_anon_or_publishable_key
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=YOUR_PROJECT_REF

# Discord OAuth (same app in Discord Developer Portal + Edge Function secrets DISCORD_CLIENT_* + VITE_DISCORD_CLIENT_ID)
#
# Redirect URL in Discord (OAuth2 → Redirects) for directory sign-in and experience verification:
# - Your site callback (required): match VITE_DISCORD_REDIRECT_URI or `{origin}/discord/callback` on your domain.
#   Experience verification (Approve/Reject) uses that same URL — you do not add a redirect per /verify/:token link.
#   Register BOTH if unsure: https://erlc.directory/discord/callback AND https://www.erlc.directory/discord/callback
#   (the app sends the host you are browsing; Discord requires an exact match).
# Sign-in uses the discord-oauth Edge Function (Discord scopes: identify + guilds only; no email from Discord).
# You may still keep https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback in Discord if you use other Supabase OAuth flows.
#
# Optional but strongly recommended in production: set the full site redirect URL so it matches
# Discord Developer Portal AND Supabase “Redirect URLs” EXACTLY (www vs preview host matters for PKCE).
# Example: https://www.erlc.directory/discord/callback
# VITE_DISCORD_REDIRECT_URI=
# Optional: defaults to a legacy ID in code if unset — should match Edge secrets.
# VITE_DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=

# Optional: override the origin used in shared links (verification URLs). Defaults to www.erlc.directory on Vercel previews.
# VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_ORIGIN=https://www.erlc.directory

# Browser redirect: *.vercel.app and apex erlc.directory → canonical site (default https://www.erlc.directory).
# Optional explicit destination (overrides default when set):
# VITE_CANONICAL_SITE_URL=https://www.erlc.directory
# On Vercel Preview, set to true if you must test on the *.vercel.app URL without redirecting:
# VITE_DISABLE_CANONICAL_HOST_REDIRECT=true

# Footer / UI
# VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
# Public Discord community link (footer "Discord" column)
# VITE_DISCORD_COMMUNITY_URL=https://discord.gg/your-invite

# Supabase Edge Function secrets (Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets), not VITE_:
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...        # Bot token; bot must share a server with users who receive DMs
# PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.erlc.directory   # Used in DM links (experience-verify, broadcasts)
# ROBLOX_OPEN_CLOUD_API_KEY=...  # Pro only: verify-roblox-pro inventory read
# Optional: ROBLOX_PRO_GAME_PASS_ID=...  # Override default Pro catalog / game pass id
# Deploy: npm run deploy:function:verify-roblox-pro
#
# Roblox OAuth (link Roblox profile — no purchase): register an app in Roblox Creator, add redirect URL exactly:
#   https://YOUR_SITE_ORIGIN/roblox/callback   (e.g. https://www.erlc.directory/roblox/callback)
# These three MUST be set as Supabase Edge Function secrets (same place as DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN). Putting them only in Vercel will not fix "Roblox sign-in is not configured" toasts.
# Supabase Edge Function secrets:
# ROBLOX_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=...
# ROBLOX_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# ROBLOX_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://www.erlc.directory/roblox/callback   # must match Creator portal + browser URL
# Deploy: npm run deploy:function:roblox-oauth-start && npm run deploy:function:roblox-oauth-complete
